WCAG Checklist
-- Perceivable --

Homepage
One thing I noticed is that some of the images don’t really explain themselves if you couldn’t see them. Like if someone was using a screen reader, they might not know what the image is about.
How it could be improved:  Just adding short descriptions to images so they can be read out properly.

Events Page
Some of the text (especially smaller text) looks kind of light compared to the background. It’s readable but not very strong.
How it could be improved:  Use slightly darker text so it stands out more and is easier to read.

Support Page
The messages (like errors or success) seem to depend a lot on colour, like red or green.
How it could be improved:  Add actual text explanations so users don’t have to rely on colour only.



-- Operable --

Navigation Bar (all pages)
When using the keyboard (tab), it’s a bit hard to tell where you are on the page sometimes.
How it could be improved:  Make it more obvious which item is selected when tabbing through.

Events Page
The event cards look clickable, but they might not fully work using just the keyboard.
How it could be improved:  Make sure everything clickable can also be accessed using keyboard controls.

Library Rooms Page
Booking or selecting rooms feels like it’s mainly designed for mouse use.
How it could be improved:  Allow users to move through booking options using only the keyboard.



-- Understandable --

Support Page (forms)
Some inputs don’t fully explain what you’re supposed to type in, especially if you’re new to the app.
How it could be improved:  Add easy to read labels or instructions for each input.

Events Page
Some buttons or actions aren’t clear at first glance.
How it could be improved:  Use easier to read wording so users know what will happen.

Navigation
The layout is mostly the same, which is good, but it’s not always obvious what page you’re currently on.
How it could be improved:  You could Highlight the current page in the navigation bar.



-- Robust --

Events Page (recommendations / filtering)
When the page updates (like showing new events), it possible it might not be obvious for screen reader users.
How it could be improved:  Make it so that when the page updates an announced is made so users know something changed.

All Pages
In some segments of the app could be made in a way that isn’t fully standard (like using general containers for buttons). And make it a bit more eye catching.
How it could be improved:  Use more structured elements so assistive tech can understand it better.


But Overall, the app is functional and is user friendly but there are a few issues with the accessibility that could affect some users. 
Some of these issues include things like keyboard navigation, confusing inputs, and some readability issues.
But when these issues are fixed this would make the app more inclusive and closer to WCAG standards.
